P/2 that allows multiple requests and responses to be sent over a single TCP connection. This is achieved by using a technique called \"streaming,\" where each request and response is associated with a unique stream identifier. Each stream can have its own priority level, allowing the server to prioritize which streams should receive more attention. Multiplexing reduces the overhead of establishing new connections for each request, making HTTP/2 faster and more efficient than HTTP/1.0.", "cited_chunk_ids": [], "refused": false, "generation_latency_seconds": 6.548339249973651}
